&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Rush Street Interactive (NYSE: RSI) is a market leader in online casino and sports betting, currently operating real-money gaming with our brands: BetRivers.com, PlaySugarHouse.com, and RushBet.co. We’re building bridges between online, social and land-based gaming businesses to create amazing, integrated experiences that keep players in the game.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As an Accounting Operations Analyst at RSI, you’ll gain hands-on experience in the dynamic world of online casino and sports betting.&amp;nbsp;In this role, you’ll build a strong foundation in our industry while supporting key accounting processes, assisting with monthly performance analysis, and contributing to ongoing operational improvements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with Accounting Operations Seniors and the Manager, you’ll help streamline workflows, learn about automation tools, and deliver meaningful support to the team.&amp;nbsp;Your work will play an important role in ensuring accurate month-end activities, processing invoices efficiently, and collaborating with cross-functional teams to support RSI’s continued growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the monthly close process by preparing journal entries for revenue streams and related operating costs, ensuring accuracy and timeliness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform reconciliations across gaming platforms, payment providers, banks, and internal ledgers; investigate and escalate discrepancies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reconcile payment provider settlements, validate fees, and follow up with vendors on variances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor user deposits, withdrawals, chargebacks, and suspicious activity, coordinating with risk and operations teams as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the preparation and analysis of financial statements and reports under IFRS and US GAAP, including variance analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support compliance with regulatory requirements across LATAM and contribute to statutory accounting and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with internal controls execution and support internal and external audit processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review contracts and regulatory updates to identify potential accounting and financial reporting impacts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and support ERP (NetSuite) processes, contributing to data accuracy and system efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities for process improvements, including automation and standardization initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a working understanding of RSI’s online gaming ecosystem (casino and sports betting) to support accounting activities in a multi-entity, multi-jurisdiction environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in accounting or finance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of relevant experience (Big4 exposure and online gaming experience is a plus!)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Excel expertise: Ability to work with large datasets, create formulas, and use key functions to support accurate analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of IFRS: Solid understanding of IFRS Generally Accepted Accounting Principles and financial reporting standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meticulous attention to detail: A commitment to accuracy and precision in every aspect of your work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organizational &amp;amp; communication skills: Ability to effectively prioritize, manage multiple tasks, and collaborate across teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NetSuite experience is a plus!.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;English proficiency at C1 level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
