&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Rush Street Interactive (NYSE: RSI) is a market leader in online casino and sports betting, currently operating real-money gaming with our brands: BetRivers.com, PlaySugarHouse.com, and RushBet.co. We’re building bridges between online, social and land-based gaming businesses to create amazing, integrated experiences that keep players in the game.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a Community Chat Ambassador, you will be responsible for overseeing and moderating interactions and dynamics within the LATAM Community Chat. Acts as a conversation starter to promote a fun, positive, and exciting environment for players. Also ensures compliance with chat rules and that site promotions are communicated clearly, in a friendly and timely manner. Finally, contributes to the creation of innovative ways to engage with customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor chat conversations to ensure community rules are respected, including regulating offensive behavior/language or rule violations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remind members of the community guidelines and ensure everyone understands and follows them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Encourage players to actively and positively participate in discussions and activities by asking questions and sparking interesting conversations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve conflicts between players impartially and constructively, seeking solutions that benefit the community environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide assistance to members who have questions or need support, fostering a welcoming atmosphere.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and analyze chat activity to identify trends, problematic behavior, and areas for improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report recurring issues or serious situations to administrators/stakeholders for further attention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather and share player feedback, highlighting both strengths and areas for improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay informed on community trends and best moderation practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate, prepare, and manage innovative promotions and events that boost engagement in the chat.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively promote marketing campaigns and platform features.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze and share communication suggestions with other team members for continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately and promptly process rewards granted through Community Chat activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in any field, or currently pursuing a degree.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ months of experience in customer service-related areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Soft skills such as empathy to understand and appropriately respond to players&#39; emotions and needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conflict resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid knowledge of the product and Community Chat rules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to assess situations and make informed decisions quickly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handling of difficult situations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aptitude for multitasking and prioritizing while maintaining an organized and controlled environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creativity, Adaptability and Flexibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to travel occasionally both domestically and international&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
