&lt;li&gt;Ensure Escalations team processes and procedures are current, well-documented, and consistently followed, identifying and driving updates as workflows, products, or regulatory requirements evolve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify opportunities for the Escalations team to add greater value to players, whether through expanded scope, improved resolution pathways, or new engagement channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain alignment between the Escalations and Training functions, ensuring Escalations-driven insights feed back into training content and

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Rush Street Interactive (NYSE: RSI) is a market leader in online casino and sports betting, currently operating real-money gaming with our brands: BetRivers.com, PlaySugarHouse.com, and RushBet.co. We’re building bridges between online, social and land-based gaming businesses to create amazing, integrated experiences that keep players in the game.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The SENA Intern will lead the construction and launch of the HR Intelligence Hub: a digital ecosystem that centralizes and standardizes RSI Colombia’s Job Descriptions and HR Vendors directory. This role goes beyond administrative support — the person in this role will build two living tools the People team will rely on daily, incorporating governance logic, inclusive language standards, and maintenance protocols that ensure long-term accuracy. The intern will work closely with the POPs team across all project phases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diagnose the current state of the Job Descriptions bank and HR Vendors directory, identifying gaps, inconsistencies, and improvement opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Standardize Job Description formats using inclusive language, a competency-based approach, and alignment with RSI’s organizational framework.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build an interactive digital repository in Confluence with version history and a leader-driven update request protocol.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Audit and update the HR Vendors bank with strategic classification, an evaluation scorecard, and a contract and compliance status tracker (active / expiring soon / expired).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct 30-minute validation sessions with area leaders for each Job Description review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design a governance protocol to ensure future maintenance of both resources without depending on a single person.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hard Skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, PowerPoint).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Confluence, SharePoint, or similar digital collaboration platforms is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional writing skills with inclusive and competency-based language standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of HR processes, document management, and administrative process design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intermediate to advanced English level (B2) preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently enrolled Professional student in Business Administration, Industry Engineering or a related field. Must be eligible to complete the SENA productive practice stage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Soft Skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and organizational skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assertive communication with leaders, vendors, and cross-functional teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Autonomous, proactive work style with a solution-oriented mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective time management and ability to prioritize multiple tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative approach and openness to feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
