&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Rush Street Interactive (NYSE: RSI) is a market leader in online casino and sports betting, currently operating real-money gaming with our brands: BetRivers.com, PlaySugarHouse.com, and RushBet.co. We’re building bridges between online, social and land-based gaming businesses to create amazing, integrated experiences that keep players in the game.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are a mobile-first organization evolving our digital platform toward a modern, scalable, event-driven architecture. As a&amp;nbsp;Sr. Front End Engineer, you will play a foundational role in building and evolving our client applications and the event orchestration architecture that powers them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role extends beyond traditional feature development. You will help architect and implement scalable client-side instrumentation frameworks, shared frontend capabilities, and integration patterns that enable structured event collection, analytics, lifecycle engagement, and downstream data systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work in close coordination with feature-delivery teams to ensure instrumentation and orchestration standards are embedded directly into product development. In parallel, you will help shape the long-term evolution of our client event architecture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position requires deep frontend and mobile expertise combined with systems thinking, architectural rigor, and a strong understanding of scalable event-driven systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Client &amp;amp; Mobile Engineering&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Frontend development across web and native mobile platforms (React, Angular, TypeScript, iOS, Android).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to and evolve a modular, scalable micro-frontend architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build reusable frontend components and shared client frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize performance and responsiveness across devices, with particular focus on mobile reliability and efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish best practices for SDK integrations, consent enforcement, observability, and client performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Event Instrumentation &amp;amp; Orchestration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement structured event instrumentation frameworks across web and mobile applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Instrument native iOS and Android applications, including analytics/CDP SDK integration with attention to performance, batching, offline handling, and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define, version, and govern structured event schemas and taxonomy standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect scalable integration patterns between client applications, backend services, and downstream data platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure event data is reliable, well-structured, and suitable for streaming, analytics, identity resolution, and activation use cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support monitoring, debugging, and continuous improvement of client event pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cross-Functional&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
